
Microsoft touts *Power Query* as a
"
   Data Connectivity and Data Preparation technology that enables business
   users to seamlessly access data stored in hundreds of data sources and
   reshape it to fit their needs, with an easy to use, engaging, and no-code
   user experience.
"

Power Query is natively integrated into
  • Microsoft Power BI
  • → Microsoft/Office/Excel (found in the *Data* tab, under *Get & Transform*)
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server/Data-Tools[Microsoft SQL Server Data Tools] for → Windows/development/Visual-Studio
  • Common Data Service

The → Microsoft/Power-Query/Editor allows to
  • preview → development/Data
  • apply over 300 data transformations

{ Mashing-up data #power-query-mashing-up-data

 *Mashing-up data* refers to the process of filtering and combining → development/Data from possible multiple data sources.

  Such mash up processes can be expressed with the → Microsoft/Power-Query/M-formula/language.

  Apparently, the *Microsoft Power Query → development/databases/OLE-DB/provider[OLE DB provider] (`Microsoft.Mashup.OleDb`) seems to be suited for mashing-up data.

}

sa:

  → development/Data/preparation

  → Microsoft/Power-Query/M-formula/language
